<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5958411-tony">Tony</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The character of Barlebooth travels the world for 20 years, painting watercolour pictures of ports. He sends these back to France to be converted into<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The character of Barlebooth travels the world for 20 years, painting watercolour pictures of ports. He sends these back to France to be converted into jigsaws. On his return, he solves the jigsaws and uses a chemical solution to 're-bind' them into paintings. Each painting, on the 20th anniversary of its creation, is dissolved, leaving only a white board. In short, he devotes his life to something that leaves absolutely no impression on the world. <br /><br />There's slightly more to it than this, but I don't want to spoil things in case you ever read the book...<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
